TASK: Diagnose and fix the figlet frame toggle bug in app/figlet_text_view.cpp.

BUG DESCRIPTION:
The right-click context menu 'Hide Frame' on TFigletTextWindow is broken:
- 1st click (Hide Frame): nothing visible happens
- 2nd click (Show Frame): figlet text disappears (blank window)  
- 3rd click (Hide Frame): figlet text comes back, but frame was never actually hidden

The frame toggle code is in TFigletTextWindow::handleEvent, case cmCtxToggleFrame (around line 223).
The window uses initFrame/initFrameless pattern with a TGhostFrame for frameless mode.

CONTEXT:
- TFigletTextWindow is in app/figlet_text_view.cpp and app/figlet_text_view.h
- It has a child TFigletTextView (figletView_) that renders the figlet art
- The frame toggle does: remove old frame, destroy it, create new frame, insertBefore(frame, figletView_), then changeBounds on figletView_
- initFrameless should return a TGhostFrame (invisible frame)
- TFrameAnimationWindow in app/test_pattern_app.cpp has identical logic and may have the same bug

COMPARE with working frame toggle patterns in the tvision codebase if helpful.

Scope:
- Files: app/figlet_text_view.cpp, app/figlet_text_view.h, app/test_pattern_app.cpp
- Look at how initFrame vs initFrameless work
- Check if frameless_ state is correctly tracked
- Check if TGhostFrame is being created properly
- Check Z-order after insert

Deliver:
1) Root cause analysis
2) Fix in app/figlet_text_view.cpp
3) If same bug exists in TFrameAnimationWindow (app/test_pattern_app.cpp), fix there too
4) Build with: cmake --build ./build --target test_pattern
5) Confirm build succeeds
